  <summary>10/10/2002--Introduced.
September 11th Assistance Tax Clarification Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income amounts paid to any person as assistance on account of any property or business damaged by, and for economic revitalization directly related to, the terrorist attacks on the United States that occurred on September 11, 2001.</summary>
